notesStmt.note: Item cataloged from digital facsimile and existing description.

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Legal treatise written as a commentary on another of al-Marghīnānī's works, Bidāyat al-mubtadiʼ. Extensive tables of contents added to beginning of work.

author.persName: Marghīnānī, ʻAlī ibn Abī Bakr, -1196 or 1197

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.extent: 478 leaves : 265 x 185 (180 x 110) mm bound to 270 x 195 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed.

binding.p: Leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); blind-stamped medallions on covers and flap; spine and flap hinge limp and damaged.

origin.p: The copy is undated; perhaps produced in the 16th or 17th century.

history.provenance: Gift of Mayer Sulzberger to the library of the Dropsie College of Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate, inside front cover).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College of Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate, inside front cover).
